original: Borg, Stig Adolf, kommimisler, Stockaryd, f. 16/11/06 i Kalmar av Carl B. o. Sofie Brolin. — Stud:ex. i Kalm. 25, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 27, teol. kand. samt prakt. teol. prov 36, prästv. f. Växjö stift 37. Tj_g. s. pastradj. i Runsten, Köping o. Ljuder, v. kommin. i Torsås, v. pastor i Karlstorp o. Rogberga, pastorsadj. i Ryda-hodm, kyrkoadj. i Norrahammar 42, kommin. i Stockaryd sed. 43.
translated: Borg, Stig Adolf was born on November 16, 1906 in Kalmar to Carl B. and Sofie Brolin. He graduated from Kalm. High School in 1925, received a degree in theology from Lund University in 1927, and completed his practical theological exam in 1936. He was ordained as a pastor for the Växjö diocese in 1937 and worked as a curate in Runsten, Köping, and Ljuder, as well as a curate in Torsås and a pastor in Karlstorp and Rogberga. He also served as a vicar in Ryda-hodm and as a church assistant in Norrahammar in 1942 before becoming a minister in Stockaryd in 1943. He married in the year of 19xx.
